<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407122>
    dc:description "FIGURE 21. Oodes gracilis A. Villa & G.B. Villa, 1833 (A–B: neotype and its labels; C–D: female specimen, Bulgaria, Pomorie-See; E–G: male specimen, Albania, Mali i Tabaroshit).A, C: habitus; B: left protarsomeres; D: pronotum and head; E: mentum; F: prosternal process; G: left metepisternum and metacoxa (arrow shows lateral end of metacoxal basal sulcus). Scale lines = 2 mm (Figs A, C); = 0.5 mm (Figs B, D, F–G); = 0.2 mm (Fig. E)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4407122/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407124>
    dc:description "FIGURE 22. Oodes gracilis A. Villa & G.B. Villa, 1833 (A–B: neotype; C: male specimen, Bulgaria, Dragoman Marsh; D–E: male specimen, Bulgaria, Srebarna Lake; F–G: female specimens, Bulgaria, Dragoman Marsh). A, C: median lobe of aedeagus, left lateral view; B, D: same, dorsal view; E: same, ventral view; F: left gonocoxite, ventral view; G: spermathecal complex and gonocoxites, ventral view. Scale lines = 0.5 mm (Figs A–E, G); = 0.2 mm (Fig. F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4407124/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

